<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-12-01T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-12-01T09:00:00-05:00" n="680" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d680">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1153 St 2/–: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hammond</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-12-01T14:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">December 1,
                                        1927—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received December 1—12:32
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>132. Department’s telegram 94, November 22, 6 p.m. The Spanish
                            Government, acting for oil monopoly, has seized without compensation
                            Alicante installations of Standard Oil subsidiary by order effective
                            today. I have informed Spanish Government that I am aware of seizure and
                            that I am reserving all rights in the premises.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hammond</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>